WEBVTT

00:00:00.300 --> 00:00:01.884
Hi, I'm Erik Hill.

00:00:01.884 --> 00:00:05.844
I build agentic AI systems that check their own work

00:00:05.844 --> 00:00:10.200
and keep a human on every step that can't be undone.

00:00:10.200 --> 00:00:15.619
Self-taught, in under a year, I built an autonomous development harness:

00:00:15.619 --> 00:00:23.500
a multi-agent loop that plans, builds, reviews, and validates its own changes to a real product.

00:00:23.500 --> 00:00:25.571
Work moves through five stages:

00:00:25.571 --> 00:00:27.643
Strategy, Execution, Critic, Evaluation, Ops.

00:00:27.643 --> 00:00:31.786
The critic runs on a colder model in fresh context

00:00:31.786 --> 00:00:38.000
so it isn't grading its own homework, and every irreversible step still waits for me.

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:40.073
The same discipline is public.

00:00:40.073 --> 00:00:45.049
This board grades sixteen models across five labs on a frozen suite.

00:00:45.049 --> 00:00:49.610
No LLM-as-judge, exact-match, so a score change means the model moved

00:00:49.610 --> 00:00:50.854
not the test.

00:00:50.854 --> 00:00:55.000
When one regresses, it opens a GitHub issue by itself.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:00:56.514
Ten public repos.

00:00:56.514 --> 00:01:01.559
Six run their real compiled code right in your browser:

00:01:01.559 --> 00:01:06.605
a RAG eval harness, a merge gate that blocks regressions

00:01:06.605 --> 00:01:08.623
an MCP tool server.

00:01:08.623 --> 00:01:17.200
Plus a game live on Google Play, and a one-character fix I merged into a twelve-year-old compiler.

00:01:17.200 --> 00:01:21.900
It's all verifiable, and one click away. egnaro9.github.io.

